item.title: Clubs and Lessons
item.dc:creator: siddhikholkar
item.content:encoded:
Vintage Cyclers

Vintage Cyclers is a leisure bicycle riding group for all ages. Join the group to take part in monthly group rides to scenic points of interests around the area. Visit our Contact page to sign up.

Road Riders

Road Riders is a sport bicycle riding group for all ages. Join the group to take part in monthly group road rides and competitions. Visit our Contact page to sign up.

Lessons

For the Love of Bikes offers three different types of lessons in an individual or group setting. If you would like to sign up for the individual or group lessons, let us know which type of lesson you are interested in by visiting our Contact Page and sending us a message.

item.title: Home
item.dc:creator: siddhikholkar
item.content:encoded:
For the love of bicycles

You can't buy happiness but you can buy a bike and that's pretty close

In our family friendly bike shop, join the vintage or road riders bicycle clubs, shop for pro gear and bicycles, and learn from the pros.

Our Shop

Our family oriented shop includes a retail store where you will be greeted by our friendly staff and make to feel right at home. You can grab a smoothie at our smoothie bar and browse all the gear you're looking to use during your next ride on the road or at the beach. You'll also fins a repair shop where our clients bring their bikes for tune ups and repairs or adjustments. While you wait, sign up for a class or one of our popular bicycle clubs

Visit Our Shop

To learn more about cycling for leisure or sport visit our blog.

View Blog

Our Clubs

Our club offers something for everyone. Our Road Riders Club offers an opportunity to participate in scheduled training rides with other athletes. Our Vintage Cycle Club offers an opportunity for leisure riders to join together and enjoy a scheduled scenic ride. Visit the clubs page to learn more, check out the riding schedule and sign up to join a ride.

item.title: Multi Column Text with Headline
item.dc:creator: siddhikholkar
item.content:encoded:
May 28, 2021
12:00 PM (UTC)
60 Minutes

Alyssa will introduce you to the important aspects of the technical side of digital photography. The lesson will teach you how to operate the various features of your digital camera so you can finally know what all those buttons actually do.

Bring your questions to the webinar for a live Q&A session.

What You'll Learn:

- Focal Length
- Shutter Speed / Exposure
- Aperture / Depth of Field

Register now

Alyssa Jackson
Photographer at GTX

I'm a natural light photographer specializing in portraits of non-models. I aim for my work to be uniquely beautiful without trying too hard. My passion is to explore my creativity while documenting significant moments in my clients' lives.

I'm based in New York and currently work at GTX Studio. I also shoot a lot of portraiture as well as assignments for agencies.

item.dc:creator: siddhikholkar
item.content:encoded:
Gear

We offer a variety of gear for your bike, clothing, and wellness. Visit our online shop. Or stop in today to check new arrivals, get your questions answered, and try out the gear.

Repair

Visit our repair shop, talk with our bike mechanics. Get your bike fixed or tuned up and ready for your next leisure or competitive ride.

Smoothi Bar

Swing by our smoothie bar to get your morning, pre-ride, or post ride boost. We offer a wide variety of smoothies using fresh ingredients and dairy alternatives.
